## ServiceLocator.has() method

Determines whether the locator has the ability to provide an implementation for the requested key.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
has<K extends Key>(key: K | Key, searchAncestors: boolean): boolean;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  key | K \| [Key](./fast-foundation.key.md) | The dependency key to lookup. |
|  searchAncestors | boolean | Indicates whether to search the entire hierarchy of service locators. |

<b>Returns:</b>

boolean
